    <div id="langToggle" onclick="toggleLang()">EN</div>

    <!-- Cover -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-600 to-purple-600 text-white text-center py-16 px-4">
        <div class="lab-tag mb-4">
            <span class="zh">历史实验室 · 定期刊第3期</span>
            <span class="en">History Lab · Periodical Issue No.3</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold serif leading-tight mb-4">
            <span class="zh">算力军备竞赛的1846年镜像</span>
            <span class="en">The 1846 Mirror of the Compute Arms Race</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl opacity-90 serif italic">
            <span class="zh">当天量资本涌入基础设施，所有人都看到了未来——但没有人算过，电从哪里来</span>
            <span class="en">When capital floods infrastructure, everyone sees the future — but nobody calculates where the electricity comes from</span>
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center gap-6 text-sm opacity-80">
            <span>📅 2026.07.23</span>
            <span>
                <span class="zh">⏱️ 阅读约18分钟</span>
                <span class="en">⏱️ 18 min read</span>
            </span>
            <span>
                <span class="zh">🧪 含互动投票</span>
                <span class="en">🧪 Interactive Polls</span>
            </span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-8 px-4 md:px-8 bg-white min-h-screen">

        <p class="first-letter text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
            <span class="zh">2026年7月22日，Alphabet交出了一份"冰火两重天"的财报：谷歌云营收暴增82%至248亿美元，远超预期；但资本支出翻倍至449亿美元，自由现金流数十年来首次转负——负59亿美元。全年CapEx指引上调至1950亿到2050亿美元，CEO皮查伊坦言："AI回报仍处于早期阶段。"同一天，OpenAI宣布启动200亿美元的"Project Camellia"数据中心项目，并将到2030年的预计算力支出上调至7500亿美元。</span>
            <span class="en">On July 22, 2026, Alphabet delivered a "fire and ice" earnings report: Google Cloud revenue surged 82% to $24.8 billion, far exceeding expectations; but capital expenditure doubled to $44.9 billion, with free cash flow turning negative for the first time in decades — minus $5.9 billion. Full-year CapEx guidance was raised to $195–205 billion, and CEO Pichai admitted: "AI returns are still in the early stages." That same day, OpenAI announced the $20 billion "Project Camellia" data center project and raised its projected compute spending through 2030 to $750 billion.</span>
        </p>
        
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
            <span class="zh">全球四大云厂商2026年合计资本支出高达7250亿美元——这个数字超过了大多数国家的GDP。但微软有800亿美元的GPU在仓库吃灰，不是芯片不够，是电闸拉不上。电力变压器交货周期从疫情前的12-16周拉长到115-130周。一天烧掉20亿美元，买回来的算力却在仓库里等电。</span>
            <span class="en">The Big Four cloud providers' combined 2026 capital expenditure has reached $725 billion — a figure exceeding most nations' GDP. Yet Microsoft has $80 billion worth of GPUs sitting idle in warehouses — not because chips are insufficient, but because the power substations aren't built. Power transformer delivery times have stretched from 12–16 weeks pre-pandemic to 115–130 weeks. Burning $2 billion a day, only to find the compute capacity they bought is waiting for electricity in a warehouse.</span>
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
            <span class="zh">181年前，英国人也经历过同样的狂热。当整个国家都在铺设铁轨时，所有人都看到了未来——但没有人问过：铁轨铺到哪里，火车从哪里来？</span>
            <span class="en">One hundred and eighty-one years ago, the British experienced the same frenzy. When the entire nation was laying rails, everyone saw the future — but nobody asked: where do the rails lead, and where do the trains come from?</span>
        </p>

        <div class="divider">
            <span class="zh">✦ ✦ ✦</span>
            <span class="en">✦ ✦ ✦</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title text-2xl font-bold serif text-gray-800">
            <span class="zh">01 抉择时刻</span>
            <span class="en">01 The Moment of Decision</span>
        </h2>

        <div class="scene-card">
            <p class="text-lg font-medium mb-4 text-blue-300">
                <span class="zh">📍 1845年秋，伦敦，英格兰银行</span>
                <span class="en">📍 Autumn 1845, London, Bank of England</span>
            </p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
                <span class="zh">你是一位42岁的乡绅投资者，刚从约克郡来到伦敦，手里攥着3000英镑积蓄——相当于你庄园十年的地租收入。</span>
                <span class="en">You are a 42-year-old gentleman investor, freshly arrived in London from Yorkshire, clutching £3,000 in savings — the equivalent of your estate's rental income for ten years.</span>
            </p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4 text-yellow-300 font-medium">
                <span class="zh">你面前的世界：</span>
                <span class="en">The world before you:</span>
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4 text-yellow-300">
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 英格兰银行刚刚把贴现率降到了<strong>2.5%</strong>——历史最低</span>
                    <span class="en">• Bank of England just cut the discount rate to <strong>2.5%</strong> — a historic low</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 1844年议会收到<strong>199份</strong>新铁路申请；1845年飙升到<strong>562份</strong>；1846年将达<strong>约800余份</strong></span>
                    <span class="en">• In 1844, Parliament received <strong>199</strong> new railway applications; in 1845 this surged to <strong>562</strong>; in 1846 it would reach <strong>800+</strong></span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 乔治·赫德森控制了<strong>1450英里</strong>铁路，约占英国总里程的<strong>三分之一</strong></span>
                    <span class="en">• George Hudson controlled <strong>1,450 miles</strong> of railway — roughly <strong>one third</strong> of Britain's total</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 赫德森刚推动通过<strong>272项</strong>铁路法案，一次性批准<strong>9500英里</strong>新铁路，资本承诺约<strong>1.32亿英镑</strong>——接近英国财政收入的一半</span>
                    <span class="en">• Hudson just pushed through <strong>272</strong> railway bills, approving <strong>9,500 miles</strong> of new rail in one sweep, with capital commitments of ~<strong>£132 million</strong> — nearly half of British fiscal revenue</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 你的邻居——一位退休牧师——把全部积蓄投进了铁路。他说："赫德森担保的铁路，不可能亏。"</span>
                    <span class="en">• Your neighbor — a retired clergyman — invested his entire savings in railways. He says: "Railways backed by Hudson can't lose."</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 达尔文、勃朗特姐妹、约翰·斯图尔特·密尔都在投资铁路。<strong>157位议员和260名牧师</strong>持有铁路股票</span>
                    <span class="en">• Darwin, the Brontë sisters, John Stuart Mill — all investing in railways. <strong>157 MPs and 260 clergymen</strong> hold railway stocks</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 但你的银行表兄悄悄告诉你：赫德森的"丰厚分红"来自<strong>发行新股</strong>——用新股东的钱付老股东的利息</span>
                    <span class="en">• But your banker cousin quietly tells you: Hudson's "generous dividends" come from <strong>issuing new shares</strong> — paying old shareholders with new investors' money</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="zh">• 窗外，泰晤士河上的蒸汽船鸣笛驶过。改变国家的技术和让投资者赚钱的交易，可能不是一回事</span>
                    <span class="en">• Outside, a steamboat horns past on the Thames. The technology that transforms a nation and the deal that makes investors rich may not be the same thing</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4 text-lg font-medium text-green-300">
                <span class="zh">此刻，你必须做出选择。</span>
                <span class="en">At this moment, you must make a choice.</span>
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="divider">
            <span class="zh">你的选择</span>
            <span class="en">Your Choice</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Four choices -->
        <div id="voting-area">
            <div class="option-card" data-option="A">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                    <span class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-green-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg shrink-0">A</span>
                    <div class="flex-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800">
                            <span class="zh">全仓铁路 —— 把全部积蓄投入赫德森旗下</span>
                            <span class="en">All-In Railways — Invest Everything in Hudson's Companies</span>
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">
                            <span class="zh">"铁路是这个时代的蒸汽机——不，它比蒸汽机更伟大。赫德森控制着三分之一的英国铁路，他不可能错。银行利率2.5%，铁路分红10%以上，这不叫投机，这叫理性。如果我不买，三年后我会后悔今天没有把所有钱都压上去。"</span>
                            <span class="en">"Railways are the steam engine of this age — no, they're greater than the steam engine. Hudson controls a third of Britain's railways; he can't be wrong. Bank rate at 2.5%, railway dividends over 10% — this isn't speculation, it's rationality. If I don't buy, I'll regret not going all-in three years from now."</span>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="option-card" data-option="B">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                    <span class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-blue-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg shrink-0">B</span>
                    <div class="flex-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800">
                            <span class="zh">精选优质线路 —— 只投已通车运营的铁路</span>
                            <span class="en">Quality Selection — Only Invest in Operating Railways</span>
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">
                            <span class="zh">"我看好铁路的未来，但我不是赌徒。那些还在纸面上的约800余份议会申请——有多少能真正建成？我选择已经通车、有真实票务收入的公司。哪怕收益低一些，至少我能看到铁轨上跑的火车，而不是图纸上的线条。"</span>
                            <span class="en">"I believe in railways' future, but I'm no gambler. Of those 800+ applications still on paper — how many will actually be built? I choose companies already running with real ticket revenue. Even if returns are lower, at least I can see trains on the tracks, not lines on blueprints."</span>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="option-card" data-option="C">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                    <span class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-yellow-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg shrink-0">C</span>
                    <div class="flex-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800">
                            <span class="zh">获利了结，持有现金 —— 卖掉已有铁路股票</span>
                            <span class="en">Take Profits, Hold Cash — Sell Existing Railway Stocks</span>
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">
                            <span class="zh">"我已经在铁路上赚了很多。但现在，连我的牧师邻居都在买铁路股票——当所有人都进场的时候，就该离场了。银行利率确实低，但至少我的本金是安全的。2.5%的利息听起来不多，但总比亏掉全部积蓄强。"</span>
                            <span class="en">"I've already made good money on railways. But now, even my clergyman neighbor is buying railway stocks — when everyone's getting in, it's time to get out. The bank rate is low, yes, but at least my principal is safe. 2.5% interest doesn't sound like much, but it beats losing everything."</span>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="option-card" data-option="D">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                    <span class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg shrink-0">D</span>
                    <div class="flex-1">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-800">
                            <span class="zh">反向做空 —— 借入铁路股票卖出，赌泡沫破裂</span>
                            <span class="en">Short Sell — Borrow Railway Shares to Sell, Bet on Bubble Burst</span>
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">
                            <span class="zh">"赫德森用新股付旧股的股息——这是庞氏骗局。约800余份议会申请、9500英里新铁路、1.32亿英镑资本承诺——接近英国财政收入的一半。任何一个有常识的人都能看出这是疯狂。我要在别人贪婪时恐惧，在泡沫破裂时大赚一笔。"</span>
                            <span class="en">"Hudson pays old dividends with new shares — it's a Ponzi scheme. 800+ applications, 9,500 miles of new rail, £132 million in capital commitments — nearly half of British fiscal revenue. Anyone with common sense can see this is madness. I'll be fearful when others are greedy, and profit hugely when the bubble bursts."</span>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Historical vote results area -->
        <div id="vote-result-area" style="display:none;">
            <div class="text-center mt-6 mb-4">
                <span class="text-green-600 font-medium">
                    <span class="zh">✓ 你的选择已记录！</span>
                    <span class="en">✓ Your choice has been recorded!</span>
                </span>
                <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm ml-2">
                    <span class="zh">继续阅读，文末还有一次预测投票</span>
                    <span class="en">Keep reading — there's one more prediction poll at the end</span>
                </span>
            </div>
            <div class="vote-stats-card">
