        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            <span class="zh">历史从来不是必然的。铁路狂热之所以以崩盘收场，是因为三个关键的"分岔点"走了特定的方向。如果它们走了另一条路，历史将完全不同。</span>
            <span class="en">History is never inevitable. The railway mania ended in a crash because three critical "forking points" took specific directions. Had they taken a different path, history would be entirely different.</span>
