                            <span class="en"><strong>If Hudson had honestly disclosed operating data</strong>, railway dividends would have collapsed in 1844. The bubble might have burst gently — a 40-50% drop instead of 85%. But railway financing would have dried up earlier, and Britain's rail network completion might have been delayed 10-15 years.</span>
