                <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800"><span class="zh">物理瓶颈取代了"铁轨瓶颈"</span><span class="en">Physical Bottlenecks Replace the "Rail Bottleneck"</span></h4>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1 text-sm"><span class="zh">1845年瓶颈是铁轨、劳动力和工程能力。2026年瓶颈是电力、变压器和水。微软800亿美元GPU吃灰——缺的不是芯片是变电站。变压器交货周期从3个月拉长到3年。IEA预测2026年全球数据中心用电可能超1000太瓦时——差不多是日本全国一年的用电量。</span><span class="en">The 1845 bottleneck was rails, labor, and engineering. The 2026 bottleneck is electricity, transformers, and water. Microsoft's $80B GPUs sit idle — not lacking chips, but substations. Transformer delivery stretched from 3 months to 3 years. IEA projects 2026 global data center electricity may exceed 1,000 TWh — roughly Japan's entire annual consumption.</span></p>
